            <thetext>HtmlArea uses for Firefox browsers a special implementation for paragraph handling. Under certain circumstances it is necessary to remove an additional paragraph (generated by Gecko) to get the correct result. This case together with content changes can lead to a wrong order of undo / redo steps.

This happens mainly if the user clicks at a certain position inside the document and performs content changes after the paragraph handling has ended.</thetext>
